  "text": "NS -not significant giogenesis vary depending on its localization, leaving this area for further research. Oral cancer is the sixth most frequent malignant neoplasm worldwide. Squamous cell carcinoma comprises the considerable majority of cases, although other histological types may also appear in that site [CITATION_1] . Adverse prognosis and still poor survival rate in spite of improvements in therapy [CITATION_2] require our attention to be focused on yet unexplained aspects of development and progression of OSCC in the hope of setting new therapeutic targets.",
